To elaborate on my last comment, the specific code which causes this SDL 2 issue is in source:src/sdl/sdl_input.c:

<pre><code class="C">
		default:
            /* TODO: SDL 2.0
			if (keysym->sym >= SDLK_WORLD_0 && keysym->sym <= SDLK_WORLD_95)
			  key = (keysym->sym - SDLK_WORLD_0) + K_WORLD_0;
            */
			break;
</code></pre>

@SDLK_WORLD_X@ were removed from SDL 2 and SDL_Scancode now looks like this: https://wiki.libsdl.org/SDL_Scancode
